UT Dallas criminology professor Robert Taylor helped develop the master's degree program at the center of a UT System investigation last year. The review found he and two other instructors awarded credits and top grades to police officers for course work they never took. They deny wrongdoing.                    

                        (University of North Texas at Dallas.)

Richard Benson, president of the University of Texas at Dallas, told the school's accreditors in a March 2018 letter "it is difficult to recreate the mind-set of the faculty who formulated and implemented this sort of a scheme."                     

                        (Vernon Bryant/Staff Photographer)

                        (Rose Baca/Staff Photographer)
